data.title: Women Writing Architecture
data.meta_description: Ayn Rand (1905–1982) was a Russian-American writer and philosopher. She is best known for her fiction, namely, The Fountainhead (1943) and Atlas Shrugged (1957), and for developing a philosophical system she named Objectivism.
